name: root
label: Annotation

name: Basic Info
detail: Basic information about the variant, such as chromosome number, position, etc.

name: ANNOVAR
detail: Pre-computed ANNOVAR annotations for all alternative SNVs based on human reference genome hg19

name: SnpEff
detail: SnpEff is a program for annotating and predicting the effects of single nucleotide polymorphisms

name: VEP
detail: Variant Effect Predictor (VEP) is developed by Ensembl and it determines the effect of the variants (SNPs, insertions, deletions, CNVs or structural variants) on genes, transcripts, and protein sequence, as well as regulatory regions.

name: AnnoQ Functional Annotations
label: PANTHER Functional Annotation
detail: Functional annotation of a variant through PANTHER API.

name: IMAGE Enhancer Linked Functional Annotations
label: PEREGRINE Functional Annotations
detail: When the variant is located in an enhancer region, the functions of its target gene inferred from the enhancer-gene links in the PEREGRINE project The ontology terms are annotated here.

name: HG19_Info
detail: Comparison from version hg19

name: chr
detail: Chromosome number of the variant."

name: pos
detail: "position (hg38)"

name: ref
detail: "reference allele"

name: alt
detail: "alternative allele"

detail: When the variant is located in an enhancer region, the assay data used to infer its link to the target genes by the PEREGRINE project are listed here. For example, single tissue eQTL, interactive TAD, ChIA-PET. These assays are usually tissue-specific. The tissue data is in the 'PEREGRINE_enhancer_linked_tissue' annotation.

name: clinvar
detail: DNA variants related to human diseases/phenotypes

name: COSMIC
detail: Catalogue Of Somatic Mutations In Cancer--Somatic coding variants discovered in cancer

name: GWAS_catalog
detail: DNA variants associated with human diseases/phenotypes discovered in GWAS Catalogue.

name: GRASP2
detail: Genome-Wide Repository of Associations Between SNPs and Phenotypes -- DNA variants associated with human diseases/phenotypes discovered in GWAS studies, including eQTLs and other quantitative trait scans

name: clinvar_MedGen_id
detail: "MedGen ID of the trait/disease the clinvar_trait referring to"

name: clinvar_OMIM_id
detail: "OMIM ID of the trait/disease the clinvar_trait referring to"

name: clinvar_Orphanet_id
detail: "Orphanet ID of the trait/disease the clinvar_trait referring to"

name: clinvar_clnsig
detail: "clinical significance by clinvar Possible values: Benign, Likely_benign, Likely_pathogenic, Pathogenic, drug_response, histocompatibility. A negative score means the score is for the ref allele"

name: clinvar_hgvs
detail: "variant in HGVS format"

name: clinvar_id
detail: "clinvar variation ID"

name: clinvar_review
detail: "ClinVar Review Status summary Possible values:  no assertion criteria provided, criteria provided, single submitter, criteria provided, multiple submitters, no conflicts, reviewed by expert panel, practice guideline"

name: clinvar_trait
detail: "the trait/disease the clinvar_clnsig referring to"

name: clinvar_var_source
detail: "source of the variant"

name: COSMIC_CNT
detail: "number of samples having this SNV in the COSMIC database"

name: COSMIC_ID
detail: "ID of the SNV at the COSMIC (Catalogue Of Somatic Mutations In Cancer) database"

name: GWAS_catalog_OR
detail: "reported odds ratio associated with strongest risk allele"

name: GWAS_catalog_pubmedid
detail: "pubmedid of the paper describing the association Please note the association is determined by rs number only, may refer to a different allele"

name: GWAS_catalog_rs
detail: "rs number according to GWAS catalog Please note the association is determined by rs number only, may refer to a different allele"

name: GWAS_catalog_trait
detail: "associated trait according to GWAS catalog. Please note the association is determined by rs number only, may refer to a different allele"

name: GRASP_PMID
detail: "PMID number by GRASP"

name: GRASP_ancestry
detail: "population ancestry of the samples on which the association test was based"

name: GRASP_p-value
detail: "p-value of the association test based on the SNP"

name: GRASP_phenotype
detail: "phenotype the SNP associated with"

name: GRASP_platform
detail: "SNP platform on which the association test was based"

name: GRASP_rs
detail: "rs number by GRASP"

name: ALSPAC_AC
detail: "Alternative allele count in called genotypes in UK10K TWINSUK cohort."

name: ALSPAC_AF
detail: "Alternative allele frequency in called genotypes in UK10K TWINSUK cohort."

name: ALSPAC_AN
detail: "Total allele count in called genotypes in UK10K TWINSUK cohort."

name: APPRIS
detail: "APPRIS annotation for the transcripts matching Ensembl_transcriptid Multiple entries separated by ";". Potential values: principal1, principal2, principal3, principal4, principal5, alternative1, alternative2. See https://useast.ensembl.org/info/genome/genebuild/transcript_quality_tags.html"

name: Aloft_Confidence
detail: "Confidence level of Aloft_pred; values can be "High Confidence" (p < 0.05) or "Low Confidence" (p > 0.05) multiple values separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: Aloft_Fraction_transcripts_affected
detail: "the fraction of the transcripts of the gene affected i.e. No. of transcripts affected by the SNP/Total no. of protein_coding transcripts for the gene multiple values separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: Aloft_pred
detail: "final classification predicted by ALoFT; values can be Tolerant, Recessive or Dominant multiple values separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: Aloft_prob_Dominant
detail: "Probability of the SNP being classified as dominant disease-causing by ALoFT multiple values separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: Aloft_prob_Recessive
detail: "Probability of the SNP being classified as recessive disease-causing by ALoFT multiple values separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: Aloft_prob_Tolerant
detail: "Probability of the SNP being classified as benign by ALoFT multiple values separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: CADD_phred
detail: "CADD phred-like score, ranges 1-99, the larger the number the more likely damaging; score >10 means the variant in the top 10% (0.1) among the total 8.6 billion possible SNVs, >20 means in the top 1%, >30 means in the top 0.1%, etc. CADD suggests a cutoff between 10 and 20 (e.g. 15)"

name: CADD_raw
detail: "CADD raw score, the larger the number the more likely damaging"

name: CADD_raw_rankscore
detail: "the rank of the CADD_raw score among all CADD_raw scores in genome"

name: DEOGEN2_pred
detail: "Prediction of DEOGEN2 score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.5."

name: DEOGEN2_rankscore
detail: "DEOGEN2 scores were ranked among all DEOGEN2 scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of DEOGEN2 scores in dbNSFP."

name: DEOGEN2_score
detail: "A deleteriousness prediction score "which incorporates heterogeneous information about the molecular effects of the variants, the domains involved, the relevance of the gene and the interactions in which it participates". It ranges from 0 to 1. The larger the score, the more likely the variant is deleterious. The authors suggest a threshold of 0.5 for separating damaging vs tolerant variants."

name: ENCODE_Dnase_cells
detail: "number of cell lines supporting a DNase I hypersensitive site"

name: ENCODE_Dnase_score
detail: "the higher the score the stronger the evidence of a DNase I hypersensitive site"

name: ENCODE_TFBS
detail: "name of the transcription factors (separated by ;) if the site is within a TFBS"

name: ENCODE_TFBS_cells
detail: "the cell lines (separated by ;) the TFBS was detected"

name: ENCODE_TFBS_score
detail: "the higher the score the stronger the evidence of the TFBS"

name: ENCODE_annotated
detail: "whether annotated by ENCODE based on funseq-0.1"

name: Ensembl_Regulatory_Build_ID
detail: "Ensembl ID for the regulatory feature"

name: Ensembl_Regulatory_Build_TFBS
detail: "transcription_factor_complex from Ensembl Regulatory Build. Multiple TF complexes separated by ","; proteins from the same complex are separated by "::""

name: Ensembl_Regulatory_Build_TFBS_matrix
detail: "Ensembl binding_matrix_stable_id"

name: Ensembl_Regulatory_Build_feature_type
detail: "genome segment prediction based on 118 cell types from ENCODE, BLUEPRINT and Roadmap. Predicted states: CTCF_Binding_Site, Enhancer, Open_chromatin, Promoter_Flanking_Region, TF_binding_site, Promoter"

name: Ensembl_geneid
detail: "Ensembl gene id"

name: Ensembl_proteinid
detail: "Ensembl protein ids Multiple entries separated by ";",  corresponding to Ensembl_transcriptids"

name: Ensembl_transcriptid

name: FANTOM5_CAGE_peak_permissive

detail: "whether the site is within a FANTOM5 phase 1+2 predicted permissive enhancer Y (Yes) or N (No)"

name: FANTOM5_enhancer_robust
detail: "whether the site is within a FANTOM5 phase 1 predicted robust enhancer Y (Yes) or N (No)"

name: FANTOM5_enhancer_target
detail: "if the site is within a FANTOM5 phase 1 predicted robust enhancer, this is the name of the FANTOM5 predicted target gene of the enhancer."

name: FATHMM_converted_rankscore
detail: "FATHMMori scores were first converted to FATHMMnew=1-(FATHMMori+16.13)/26.77, then ranked among all FATHMMnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of FATHMMnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented. The scores range from 0 to 1."

name: FATHMM_pred
detail: "If a FATHMMori score is <=-1.5 (or rankscore >=0.81332) the corresponding nsSNV is predicted as "D(AMAGING)"; otherwise it is predicted as "T(OLERATED)". Multiple predictions separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: FATHMM_score
detail: "FATHMM default score (weighted for human inherited-disease mutations with Disease Ontology) (FATHMMori). Scores range from -16.13 to 10.64. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: GENCODE_basic
detail: "Whether the transcript belongs to GENCODE_basic (5' and 3' complete transcripts). Multiple entries separated by ";", matching Ensembl_transcriptid. See https://useast.ensembl.org/info/genome/genebuild/transcript_quality_tags.html"

name: GERP_NR
detail: "GERP++ neutral rate"

name: GERP_RS
detail: "GERP++ RS score, the larger the score, the more conserved the site"

name: GERP_RS_rankscore
detail: "the rank of the GERP_RS score among all GERP_RS scores in genome"

name: LRT_Omega
detail: "estimated nonsynonymous-to-synonymous-rate ratio (Omega, reported by LRT)"

name: LRT_converted_rankscore
detail: "LRTori scores were first converted as LRTnew=1-LRTori*0.5 if Omega<1, or LRTnew=LRTori*0.5 if Omega>=1. Then LRTnew scores were ranked among all LRTnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank over the total number of the scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0.00162 to 0.8433."

name: LRT_pred
detail: "LRT prediction, D(eleterious), N(eutral) or U(nknown), which is not solely determined by the score."

name: LRT_score
detail: "The original LRT two-sided p-value (LRTori), ranges from 0 to 1."

name: M-CAP_pred
detail: "Prediction of M-CAP score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.025."

name: M-CAP_rankscore
detail: "M-CAP scores were ranked among all M-CAP scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of M-CAP scores in dbNSFP."

name: M-CAP_score
detail: "M-CAP score (details in DOI: 10.1038/ng.3703). Scores range from 0 to 1. The larger the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect."

name: MPC_rankscore
detail: "MPC scores were ranked among all MPC scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MPC scores in dbNSFP."

name: MPC_score
detail: "A deleteriousness prediction score for missense variants based on regional missense constraint. The range of MPC score is 0 to 5. The larger the score, the more likely the variant is pathogenic. Details see doi: http://dx.doi.org/10.1101/148353. Multiple entries are separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_transcriptid."

name: MVP_rankscore
detail: "MVP scores were ranked among all MVP scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MVP scores in dbNSFP."

name: MVP_score
detail: "A pathogenicity prediction score for missense variants using deep learning approach. The range of MVP score is from 0 to 1. The larger the score, the more likely the variant is pathogenic. The authors suggest thresholds of 0.7 and 0.75 for separating damaging vs tolerant variants in constrained genes (ExAC pLI >=0.5) and non-constrained genes (ExAC pLI<0.5), respectively. Details see doi: http://dx.doi.org/10.1101/259390 Multiple entries are separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_transcriptid."

name: MetaLR_pred
detail: "Prediction of our MetaLR based ensemble prediction score,"T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.5. The rankscore cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.81101."

name: MetaLR_rankscore
detail: "MetaLR scores were ranked among all MetaLR scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MetaLR scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1."

name: MetaLR_score
detail: "Our logistic regression (LR) based ensemble prediction score, which incorporated 10 scores (SIFT, PolyPhen-2 HDIV, PolyPhen-2 HVAR, GERP++, MutationTaster, Mutation Assessor, FATHMM, LRT, SiPhy, PhyloP) and the maximum frequency observed in the 1000 genomes populations. Larger value means the SNV is more likely to be damaging. Scores range from 0 to 1."

name: MetaSVM_pred
detail: "Prediction of our SVM based ensemble prediction score,"T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0. The rankscore cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.82257."

name: MetaSVM_rankscore
detail: "MetaSVM scores were ranked among all MetaSVM scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MetaSVM scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1."

name: MetaSVM_score
detail: "Our support vector machine (SVM) based ensemble prediction score, which incorporated 10 scores (SIFT, PolyPhen-2 HDIV, PolyPhen-2 HVAR, GERP++, MutationTaster, Mutation Assessor, FATHMM, LRT, SiPhy, PhyloP) and the maximum frequency observed in the 1000 genomes populations. Larger value means the SNV is more likely to be damaging. Scores range from -2 to 3 in dbNSFP."

name: Motif_breaking
detail: "whether break a known motif (in-house script)"

name: MutPred_AAchange
detail: "Amino acid change used for MutPred_score calculation."

name: MutPred_Top5features
detail: "Top 5 features (molecular mechanisms of disease) as predicted by MutPred with p values. MutPred_score > 0.5 and p < 0.05 are referred to as actionable hypotheses. MutPred_score > 0.75 and p < 0.05 are referred to as confident hypotheses. MutPred_score > 0.75 and p < 0.01 are referred to as very confident hypotheses."

name: MutPred_protID
detail: "UniProt accession or Ensembl transcript ID used for MutPred_score calculation."

name: MutPred_rankscore
detail: "MutPred scores were ranked among all MutPred scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MutPred scores in dbNSFP."

name: MutPred_score
detail: "General MutPred score. Scores range from 0 to 1. The larger the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect."

name: MutationAssessor_pred
detail: "MutationAssessor's functional impact of a variant - predicted functional, i.e. high ("H") or medium ("M"), or predicted non-functional, i.e. low ("L") or neutral ("N"). The MAori score cutoffs between "H" and "M", "M" and "L", and "L" and "N", are 3.5, 1.935 and 0.8, respectively. The rankscore cutoffs between "H" and "M", "M" and "L", and "L" and "N", are 0.9307, 0.52043 and 0.19675, respectively."

name: MutationAssessor_score
detail: "MutationAssessor functional impact combined score (MAori). The score ranges from -5.17 to 6.49 in dbNSFP. Multiple entries are separated by ";", corresponding to Uniprot_entry."

name: MutationTaster_AAE
detail: "MutationTaster predicted amino acid change."

name: MutationTaster_converted_rankscore
detail: "The MTori scores were first converted. If the prediction is "A" or "D" MTnew=MTori; if the prediction is "N" or "P", MTnew=1-MTori. Then MTnew scores were ranked among all MTnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores of a SNV, only the largest MTnew was used in ranking. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MTnew scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0.08979 to 0.81001."

name: MutationTaster_model
detail: "MutationTaster prediction models."

name: MutationTaster_pred
detail: "MutationTaster prediction, "A" ("disease_causing_automatic"), "D" ("disease_causing"), "N" ("polymorphism") or "P" ("polymorphism_automatic"). The score cutoff between "D" and "N" is 0.5 for MTnew and 0.31733 for the rankscore."

name: MutationTaster_score
detail: "MutationTaster p-value (MTori), ranges from 0 to 1. Multiple scores are separated by ";". Information on corresponding transcript(s) can be found by querying http://www.mutationtaster.org/ChrPos.html"

name: ORegAnno_PMID
detail: "the PMID of the paper describing the regulation"

name: ORegAnno_type
detail: "the type of regulatory region by ORegAnno"

name: PROVEAN_converted_rankscore
detail: "PROVEANori were first converted to PROVEANnew=1-(PROVEANori+14)/28, then ranked among all PROVEANnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the PROVEANnew score over the total number of PROVEANnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented. The scores range from 0 to 1."

name: PROVEAN_pred
detail: "If PROVEANori <= -2.5 (rankscore>=0.54382) the corresponding nsSNV is predicted as "D(amaging)"; otherwise it is predicted as "N(eutral)". Multiple predictions separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: PROVEAN_score
detail: "PROVEAN score (PROVEANori). Scores range from -14 to 14. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: PrimateAI_pred
detail: "Prediction of PrimateAI score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.803."

name: PrimateAI_rankscore
detail: "PrimateAI scores were ranked among all PrimateAI scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of PrimateAI scores in dbNSFP."

name: PrimateAI_score
detail: "A pathogenicity prediction score for missense variants based on common variants of non-human primate species using a deep neural network. The range of PrimateAI score is 0 to 1. The larger the score, the more likely the variant is pathogenic. The authors suggest a threshold of 0.803 for separating damaging vs tolerant variants. Details see https://doi.org/10.1038/s41588-018-0167-z"

name: RegulomeDB_motif
detail: "motif the SNP resides (from RegulomeDB) multiple values separated by ";""

name: RegulomeDB_score
detail: "categorical score from RegulomeDB. The smaller, the more likely the SNP affects binding"

name: Reliability_index
detail: "Number of observed component scores (except the maximum frequency in the 1000 genomes populations) for MetaSVM and MetaLR. Ranges from 1 to 10. As MetaSVM and MetaLR scores are calculated based on imputed data, the less missing component scores, the higher the reliability of the scores and predictions."

name: SIFT4G_converted_rankscore
detail: "SIFT4G scores were first converted to SIFT4Gnew=1-SIFT4G, then ranked among all SIFT4Gnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the SIFT4Gnew score over the total number of SIFT4Gnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented."

name: SIFT4G_pred
detail: "If SIFT4G is < 0.05 the corresponding nsSNV is predicted as "D(amaging)"; otherwise it is predicted as "T(olerated)". Multiple scores separated by ",", corresponding to Ensembl_transcriptid"

name: SIFT4G_score
detail: "SIFT 4G score (SIFT4G). Scores range from 0 to 1. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ",", corresponding to Ensembl_transcriptid"

name: SIFT_converted_rankscore
detail: "SIFTori scores were first converted to SIFTnew=1-SIFTori, then ranked among all SIFTnew scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank the SIFTnew score over the total number of SIFTnew scores in dbNSFP. If there are multiple scores, only the most damaging (largest) rankscore is presented. The rankscores range from 0.00964 to 0.91255."

name: SIFT_pred
detail: "If SIFTori is smaller than 0.05 (rankscore>0.39575) the corresponding nsSNV is predicted as "D(amaging)"; otherwise it is predicted as "T(olerated)". Multiple predictions separated by ";""

name: SIFT_score
detail: "SIFT score (SIFTori). Scores range from 0 to 1. The smaller the score the more likely the SNP has damaging effect. Multiple scores separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid."

name: TSL

name: fathmm-MKL_coding_rankscore
detail: "the rank of the fathmm-MKL_coding_score among all fathmm-MKL_coding_scores in genome"

name: fathmm-MKL_coding_score
detail: "fathmm-MKL coding prediction probability, the larger the number the more likely damaging the threshold separating deleterious prediction and neutral prediction is 0.5."

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_group

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_pred

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_rankscore
detail: "the rank of the fathmm-MKL_non-coding_score among all fathmm-MKL_non-coding_scores in genome"

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_score

name: refcodon

name: ultra_sensitive

name: MutationAssessor_rankscore
detail: "MAori scores were ranked among all MAori scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MAori scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1."

name: MetaRNN_score
detail: "Our recurrent neural network (RNN) based ensemble prediction score, which incorporated 16 scores (SIFT, Polyphen2_HDIV, Polyphen2_HVAR, MutationAssessor, PROVEAN, VEST4, M-CAP, REVEL, MutPred, MVP, PrimateAI, DEOGEN2, CADD, fathmm-XF, Eigen and GenoCanyon), 8 conservation scores (GERP, phyloP100way_vertebrate, phyloP30way_mammalian, phyloP17way_primate, phastCons100way_vertebrate, phastCons30way_mammalian, phastCons17way_primate and SiPhy), and allele frequency information from the 1000 Genomes Project (1000GP), ExAC, and gnomAD. Larger value means the SNV is more likely to be damaging. Scores range from 0 to 1."

name: MetaRNN_rankscore
detail: "MetaRNN scores were ranked among all MetaRNN scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of MetaRNN scores in dbNSFP. The scores range from 0 to 1."

name: MetaRNN_pred
detail: "Prediction of our MetaRNN based ensemble prediction score,"T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.5. The rankscore cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.6149."

name: BayesDel_addAF_score
detail: "A deleteriousness preidction meta-score for SNVs and indels with inclusion of MaxAF. See https://doi.org/10.1002/humu.23158 for details. The range of the score in dbNSFP is from -1.11707 to 0.750927. The higher the score, the more likely the variant is pathogenic. The author suggested cutoff between deleterious ("D") and tolerated ("T") is 0.0692655."

name: BayesDel_addAF_rankscore
detail: "BayesDel_addAF scores were ranked among all BayesDel_addAF scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of BayesDel_addAF scores in dbNSFP."

name: BayesDel_addAF_pred
detail: "Prediction of BayesDel_addAF score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.0692655."

name: BayesDel_noAF_score
detail: "A deleteriousness preidction meta-score for SNVs and indels without inclusion of MaxAF. See https://doi.org/10.1002/humu.23158 for details. The range of the score in dbNSFP is from -1.31914 to 0.840878. The higher the score, the more likely the variant is pathogenic. The author suggested cutoff between deleterious ("D") and tolerated ("T") is -0.0570105."

name: BayesDel_noAF_rankscore
detail: "BayesDel_noAF scores were ranked among all BayesDel_noAF scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of BayesDel_noAF scores in dbNSFP."

name: BayesDel_noAF_pred
detail: "Prediction of BayesDel_noAF score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is -0.0570105."

name: LIST-S2_score
detail: "A deleteriousness preidction score for nonsynonymous SNVs. See https://doi.org/10.1093/nar/gkaa288. for details. The range of the score in dbNSFP is from 0 to 1. The higher the score, the more likely the variant is pathogenic. The author suggested cutoff between deleterious ("D") and tolerated ("T") is 0.85."

name: LIST-S2_rankscore
detail: "LIST-S2 scores were ranked among all LIST-S2 scores in dbNSFP. The rankscore is the ratio of the rank of the score over the total number of LIST-S2 scores in dbNSFP."

name: LIST-S2_pred
detail: "Prediction of LIST-S2 score based on the authors' recommendation, "T(olerated)" or "D(amaging)". The score cutoff between "D" and "T" is 0.85."
